# Release Packaging Policy

Whenever the user asks to "release", "打包发布", "发 release", "cut a version", or similar, **you must build and attach all platform artifacts listed below to the GitHub Release**. Never ship a release with only macOS arm64.

## Required artifacts per release

| Platform | Arch | Artifact name (`<version>` = e.g. `v0.1.1`) | How it's built |
|---|---|---|---|
| macOS | arm64 (Apple Silicon) | `GripLite-<version>-darwin-arm64.dmg` | `wails build -platform darwin/arm64` on macOS |
| macOS | amd64 (Intel) | `GripLite-<version>-darwin-amd64.dmg` | Cross-compile from macOS — works with Wails 2.12 |
| Windows | amd64 | `GripLite-<version>-windows-amd64.zip` (contains `GripLite.exe`) | Cross-compile from macOS — works with Wails 2.12 |

> If any platform build fails, **do not silently skip it** — surface the error to the user and ask whether to proceed without that platform.

## Build commands

All builds inject version + date via ldflags:

```bash
BUILD_DATE=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)
LDFLAGS="-X main.buildVersion=<version> -X main.buildDate=$BUILD_DATE"
```

Use these exact targets:

```bash
~/go/bin/wails build -clean -platform darwin/arm64   -ldflags "$LDFLAGS"
~/go/bin/wails build        -platform darwin/amd64   -ldflags "$LDFLAGS"
~/go/bin/wails build        -platform windows/amd64  -ldflags "$LDFLAGS"
```

> Only the first call uses `-clean` so the frontend isn't rebuilt three times.

## Packaging

- **macOS** — wrap `build/bin/GripLite.app` in a DMG via `hdiutil create -volname "GripLite <version>" -srcfolder <staging> -ov -format UDZO <file>.dmg`. Include an `Applications` symlink in the staging dir.
- **Windows** — zip `build/bin/GripLite.exe`.

Put all artifacts under `dist/` (which is gitignored).

## Release workflow

1. Commit any outstanding changes and push `main`.
2. Tag the release (`git tag -a <version> -m "..."` + `git push origin <version>`).
3. Run `./scripts/release.sh <version>` — this is the canonical path; it performs steps 3–5. Only fall back to manual commands if the script is missing.
4. Create the GitHub release with `gh release create <version> --title "GripLite <version>" --notes "..." dist/*.dmg dist/*.zip`.
5. Verify with `gh release view <version> --json assets` that **all three files** are listed.

## Authentication

`gh` token is stored in macOS Keychain. If `gh auth status` fails, re-authenticate with:

```bash
TOKEN=$(printf "protocol=https\nhost=github.com\n\n" | git credential fill | awk -F= '/^password=/{print $2}')
echo "$TOKEN" | gh auth login --hostname github.com --with-token
```

## Release notes template

Every release's notes must include:
- **Highlights** — what's new / fixed
- **Download table** with one row per artifact + platform
- **macOS note** about unsigned Gatekeeper bypass (`xattr -dr com.apple.quarantine`)

Example:

```markdown
### Download
| Platform | File |
|---|---|
| macOS (Apple Silicon) | `GripLite-v0.1.2-darwin-arm64.dmg` |
| macOS (Intel) | `GripLite-v0.1.2-darwin-amd64.dmg` |
| Windows x64 | `GripLite-v0.1.2-windows-amd64.zip` |
```
